I’ll be completely honest with you guys. I don’t post much about my favorite irl places. It’s because I go there to get away from daily life; these places are my sanctuary. 

I’m sharing this gem because @tperezwine is a dear friend of mine who deserves the recognition of creating such an elevated & decadent menu while simultaneously birthing an intimate & elegant space in which to enjoy. ✨ 

He hand picks wines from around the world (that you cannot purchase anywhere else in TX) and brings his sommelier training and extensive world travel experiences directly to your table. 🍷 

⭐️ @planeandlevel sources only the FINEST ingredients and prepares each dish to perfection. Enjoy luxury staples such as Ossetra Caviar, Jámon Ibérico, Japanese A-5 Wagyu Beef, Fois Gras, & Black Truffle. ⭐️

Experience an entire menu of creative WINE based cocktails along with curated wine pairings and customized wine tastings. 🍷

There is no stone left unturned here at @planeandlevel 🙌 This place is very near and dear to my heart! So when you see me here, be sure to say hey & cheers! 🥂

📍 Plane & Level
203 Midway St
Old Town Spring, 77373

🥂 Champagne & Oyster Tuesdays 
🎶 Paella & Rosé Saturdays

🌱 Vegetarian & Pescatarian Options Available

🍴Thank you all who attended our Chef’s Table Tour of Italy 🇮🇹 last night! Another sold out event that was filled with great food, amazing wines and incredible people. @chefyayo6 created a delicious menu and @tperezwine always on point with the special wine pairings 🍷. Hope those of you who received the Artist Menu enjoy it as much as @sooztheartist enjoy making it for all. We are excited to start planning the next one… any suggestions on the cuisine? #oldtownspring #otstexas #planeandlevel #chefstable #houstonfoodie #houstoneats #houstonfinedining

Let’s travel to Italy by @planeandlevel 🇮🇹

This is the first time I visit a Chef’s Table at Plane and Level (once a month) and I can’t be happier after trying a high quality food curated by the one and only @chefyayo6 with the wine pairing from the Sommelier @tperezwine 🧡

This was the menu, please don’t drool the screen ok? Here we go:

1. Grilled nectarines, Sicilian olive oil, fennel pollen, whipped ricotta, crostini, hazelnuts
2. Wagyu beef carpaccio, parmigiano reggiano gelato, artichoke, black truffle
3. Burrata & eggplant, mollica, basil chips
4. Intermezzo: Campari granita
5. 1000-layer lasagne napoletana, beef & pork ragu, bechamel, mozzarella di buffalo, parmigiano reggiano
6. Porcini mushroom risotto, seared branzino 
7. Tiramisu, coffee tuile, black cocoa

Will you come with me for the next edition?

Coming up on Saturday October 21, 2023, Plane & Level is hosting a wine makers dinner with master sommelier Emmanuel Kemiji of Clos Pissarra of Spain. 

Co-Founder/Sommelier Thomas Perez and Culinary Director Orlando Amaro, have orchestrated a magical experience for this special dinner.

Starting at 3:00 p.m. with a Miura Vineyards wine tasting followed by the Basque inspired dinner at 6:00pm. @planeandlevel @chefyayo6 #thewoodlandstexas #ht #houston #ots #oldtownspring

Last night at Plane & Level, we embarked on a journey through vineyards with Foppa Ambrosi @tfawines , wines created by young Brazilian winemakers in Napa Valley. The ambiance was set aglow by the exquisite flavors of their Syrah, making it an unforgettable wine tasting experience. Thanks to co-founder/sommelier Thomas Perez who orchestrated this wonderful evening for our special guests.

To add an extra layer of creativity, fine artist Susie Cortez graced the evening with a live painting. Here’s to the artistry of winemaking and the visual poetry painted by Susie! 🍷🎨✨ #winetasting #foppaambrosi #napavalleywines #liveart #oldtownspringtx #thewoodlands #planeandlevel
